we have four-- 1, 2, 3, 4.

00:43:58.590 --> 00:44:00.010
How many in higher?

00:44:00.010 --> 00:44:00.892
AUDIENCE: Two.

00:44:00.892 --> 00:44:01.850
CATHERINE DRENNAN: Two.

00:44:01.850 --> 00:44:03.370
Up here.

00:44:03.370 --> 00:44:10.720
For carbon, we had six-- 1,
2, 3, 4, 5, 6-- two in higher.

00:44:10.720 --> 00:44:16.080
And so the bond order here was
1, the bond order here was 2.

00:44:16.080 --> 00:44:19.000
Which is more stable?

00:44:19.000 --> 00:44:22.496
Higher dissociation energy,
which one do you think?

00:44:22.496 --> 00:44:23.412
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:44:23.412 --> 00:44:24.680
CATHERINE DRENNAN: Carbon.

00:44:24.680 --> 00:44:25.310
Right.

00:44:25.310 --> 00:44:27.100
Has a bond order of two.

00:44:27.100 --> 00:44:31.150
It has more electrons in
lower energy orbitals.

00:44:31.150 --> 00:44:35.000
So it cannot really well
out of this bonding deal,

00:44:35.000 --> 00:44:43.350
and the dissociation energy for
B2, 289, whereas, for C2, 599.

00:44:43.350 --> 00:44:49.000
So when molecules come together
such that more of the electrons

00:44:49.000 --> 00:44:52.270
are in lower energy
or bonding orbitals,

00:44:52.270 --> 00:44:54.630
you form a nice,
stable molecule.

00:44:54.630 --> 00:44:57.950
When molecules come
together such that more

00:44:57.950 --> 00:45:01.750
of their electrons are an
antibonding or higher energy,

00:45:01.750 --> 00:45:03.660
that's not a happy molecule.

00:45:03.660 --> 00:45:06.840
So I'll just and with one
way to think about this.

00:45:06.840 --> 00:45:09.990
In this cartoon
molecular, break up lines,

00:45:09.990 --> 00:45:14.950
sometimes two atoms just
have an incompatible number

00:45:14.950 --> 00:45:16.880
of valence electrons.

00:45:16.880 --> 00:45:19.960
And there are just too many--
just here this molecule saying,

00:45:19.960 --> 00:45:20.830
I'm sorry.

00:45:20.830 --> 00:45:24.560
Too many of your electrons
are in my antibonding regions.

00:45:24.560 --> 00:45:27.050
I don't know how many
times we've all heard that,

00:45:27.050 --> 00:45:32.610
but it's time to dissociate, but
our atomic orbitals, well, they

00:45:32.610 --> 00:45:34.360
can still be friends.

00:45:34.360 --> 00:45:34.870
OK.

